Anglo American, Exxaro, Optimum: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-07-25T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/anglo-american-exxaro-optimum-coal-may-move-in-early-johannesburg-trade.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index fell 109.49, or 0.3
percent, to 32,016.30, by the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg on
July 22.  Anglo American Plc (AGL)  ,  Exxaro Resources Ltd. (EXX)  ,  Optimum Coal Holdings (OPT)  Ltd: South African workers
today started a strike over pay at mines producing coal for use
on local, Indian and European power plants.  Anglo American shares rose 3.34 rand, or 1 percent, to
335.46 rand. Exxaro dropped 50 cents, or 0.3 percent, to 186.50
rand. Optimum slipped 51 cents, or 2 percent, to 24.99 rand.  Anglo American Platinum Ltd. (AMS SJ): The world’s largest
platinum producer is scheduled to release first-half earnings.
The stock was unchanged at 601 rand.  Hulamin Ltd. (HLM)  : Africa’s largest aluminum processor
reports first-half results. The company said on July 13 that
earnings will be from 21 cents to 23 cents a share compared with
11 cents a year earlier. The shares surged 60 cents, or 8.2
percent, to 7.95 rand.  The following companies will start trading today without
the right to a dividend:  Avusa Ltd. (AVU)  ,  Investec Ltd. (INL)  ,  Investec Plc (INVP)  ,  MiX Telematics Ltd. (MIX)  , and
 Reunert Ltd. (RLZP)  .  To contact the reporter on this story:
